Finding the perfect birthday gift for someone you don't know very well can be a daunting task. If this is your dilemma, you have come to the right place! Whether you are looking for something small to let him know you care or something a bit more creative and special, there are many ways to give a thoughtful gift that won't break the bank. Let's take a look at some of the best options for celebrating his birthday.
__Gift Cards__: If you are stumped on what to buy, an easy solution is to give him a gift card. This way he can pick out exactly what he wants or needs without feeling as if he owes you anything in return. Gift cards to Amazon, Best Buy, or even his favorite restaurant are surefire winners that will show him that you put thought into his present.
__Alcoholic Beverages__: Buying beer or wine is an easy way to show appreciation without getting too personal. If he loves craft beers, consider buying him a few of his favorites or introducing him to something new; if he likes wine, find out what kind of red and white wines he enjoys most. If possible, pick up two bottles—one for now and one for later—so that it looks like more than just an afterthought.
__Small Token Gifts__: A great way to show someone you care is by giving them something meaningful but not overly expensive—like a book they may enjoy or tickets to their favorite event such as a movie, concert, or sports game. A unique cufflink set can also make an excellent addition if your budget allows it. No matter what type of gift you decide on, adding a personalized note with your present will help make it extra special and memorable for him.
No matter which type of gift you choose in the end, remember that it should reflect both who the person is and how much effort went into finding it. By taking the time to find something thoughtful and creative, your birthday present will be sure to leave an impression on anyone who receives it! So get creative and have fun shopping around until you find the perfect gift!